text.tspan: In modern decks, this card shows a
couple embracing. Ihave followed an
older tradition showing suitor
apparently choosing between two
women. This card represents choice,
the sort of choice where both
alternatives are attractive and one
must be abandoned forever. This
reflects a reality of mediaeval
life, which is that your choice of
lover is significant (think doweries
and family alliances) and
irrevocable in a way it is not in
modern times.
To emphasize the choice aspect I
show the two women standing on
different branches of a forked path.
The vaguely Victorian clothing is
the result of my whimsical decision
around the time Iwas drawing the
Magician that the trumps would all
be wearing hats of some sort. When
it came to dressing a suitor, a top
hat just seemed appropriate.
